cmm0eqyra0010s2scoaokv2e1	cmm0eqyqm0000s2scocwcsg1i	6.1	non_compliant	85	The HTML provided contains multiple issues that suggest non-compliance with web accessibility standards. These include but are not limited to:\n1. The HTML structure seems incomplete, as the provided code snippet is cut off and lacks a closing tag for the SVG element (<svg>). This could potentially cause issues with the proper rendering of the content.\n2. There are multiple instances where ARIA roles are used without corresponding ARIA properties, such as `role="button"` without `aria-label` or `aria-labelledby`. This can make it difficult for screen readers to convey the purpose of these elements to users with visual impairments.\n3. Some elements lack appropriate ARIA attributes, such as `<a>` tags without `aria-describedby` or `aria-labelledby`, which can also impact accessibility for users who rely on assistive technologies.\n4. The provided code does not appear to include any semantic HTML elements (e.g., <header>, <nav>, <main>, <footer>) that help structure the content and improve its accessibility.	[{"type": "issue", "message": "Incomplete HTML structure"}, {"type": "issue", "message": "Missing ARIA properties for some roles"}, {"type": "issue", "message": "Lack of appropriate ARIA attributes on some elements"}, {"type": "issue", "message": "Absence of semantic HTML elements"}]	["Ensure that all HTML elements have proper closing tags and are properly nested.", "Provide ARIA properties for all roles to improve accessibility for screen reader users.", "Include appropriate ARIA attributes on all interactive elements (e.g., `<a>`, `<button>`) to enhance their accessibility.", "Use semantic HTML elements to structure the content and improve its accessibility for all users."]	ai	52	\N
